 \lim_{r \to \infty} \int_0^{{\pi/2}} e^{-r \sin \theta}d\theta =  \int_0^{{\pi/2}}\lim_{r \to \infty} e^{-r \sin \theta}d\theta = \int_0^{\pi/2}0 d\theta = 0. 
